## 2. Complete Execution Flow

```
User uploads a Lost/Found report (with image)
         │
         ▼
lostItemController.js → foundItemController.js
  → await aiOrchestrator.processAndMatchReport(item, type)
         │
         ▼
aiOrchestrator.js → embeddingPipeline.processReport(title, desc, hasImage, imagePath)
         │
         ▼ (calls FastAPI on http://localhost:8000)
         │
         ├─── processImageDocument(imagePath)
         │         EasyOCR → reads text from image
         │         spaCy NER → extracts name, roll, bank, etc.
         │         Returns: { ocrText, detectedEntities, isSensitive }
         │
         ├─── generateImageEmbedding(imagePath)
         │         OpenCLIP ViT-B-32 → produces 512-dim vector
         │         Returns: { embedding: float[512], latency }
         │
         └─── generateTextEmbedding("title + description + ocrSummary")
                   Sentence Transformer all-MiniLM-L6-v2 → 384-dim vector
                   Returns: { embedding: float[384], latency }
         │
         ▼
aiOrchestrator.js
  → Saves OCR results to MongoDB (isSensitive, ocrText, detectedEntities)
         │
         ▼
qdrantService.upsertVector('text_embeddings', id, textEmbedding, payload)
  → PUT http://localhost:6333/collections/text_embeddings/points
         │
         ▼
qdrantService.upsertVector('image_embeddings', id, imageEmbedding, payload)   [only if image exists]
  → PUT http://localhost:6333/collections/image_embeddings/points
         │
         ▼
matchingService.findMatches()
  → Searches Qdrant for opposite-type candidates
  → Hybrid scoring: Image sim + Semantic sim + Category + Location + Date
  → If score ≥ 40 → Match document saved in MongoDB
  → Notifications created for both users
```

