## 3. Where Vectors Are Physically Stored on Disk

All Qdrant data lives here on your computer:

```
c:\Users\BAVISHYA\Desktop\lost-and-found\backend\qdrant-bin\
├── qdrant.exe                   ← The database server binary
├── .qdrant-initialized          ← First-run marker
├── snapshots\                   ← EMPTY (manual exports only, none taken yet)
│   ├── image_embeddings\
│   ├── text_embeddings\
│   └── tmp\
└── storage\                     ← THIS IS WHERE YOUR VECTORS LIVE
    ├── raft_state.json          ← Cluster consensus state
    ├── aliases\                 ← Collection aliases (none configured)
    └── collections\
        ├── image_embeddings\
        │   ├── config.json      ← Collection config (size:512, Cosine distance)
        │   ├── version.info
        │   └── 0\              ← Shard 0 (single shard)
        │       ├── shard_config.json
        │       ├── replica_state.json
        │       ├── wal\         ← Write-Ahead Log (WAL)
        │       │   ├── open-1  ← 32MB WAL segment (upserted vectors buffer here)
        │       │   └── open-2  ← Second WAL segment
        │       └── segments\   ← 8 segments (each a self-contained vector index)
        │           ├── 4c768f31.../
        │           ├── 4f995a68.../
        │           └── ... (6 more)
        └── text_embeddings\
            ├── config.json      ← Collection config (size:384, Cosine distance)
            └── 0\
                ├── wal\
                └── segments\   ← 8 segments
```

### What files contain the actual vectors?

| File/Folder | Contents |
|---|---|
| `wal/open-1`, `wal/open-2` | **Newly upserted vectors** — they are written here first (32 MB buffers) |
| `segments/<uuid>/` | **Flushed, indexed vectors** — once WAL is flushed, data moves here into binary segment files |
| `config.json` | Collection configuration (dimension size, distance metric, HNSW settings) |

### Why is `snapshots/` empty?
Snapshots are **manual exports** — they are only created when you explicitly call `POST /collections/image_embeddings/snapshots`. They are not automatic. Since you haven't triggered a snapshot, those folders are empty. Snapshots are just backup exports (like a `.zip` of the collection); your actual data is in `storage/collections/`.

